<h1 class="x-h1">Addons</h1>

<div class="x-block-full">
    <p>Addons allow you to add additional functionality to a widget without having to create a whole new widget type.  This works well if you need to tweak functionality or add new features.</p>
</div>

<div class="x-block-full">
    <h2 class="x-h2">Instantiating Addons</h2>
    <p>Addons can be instantiated using the <code>data-addons</code> property.  Multiple addons can be loaded at the same time, separated by a space:</p>

    <pre><code>
        &lt;div data-widget-type="tab" <b>data-addons="tab-animation"</b>&gt;
            &lt;ul&gt;
                &lt;li&gt;&lt;a&gt;Tab 1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
                &lt;li&gt;&lt;a&gt;Tab 2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
                &lt;li&gt;&lt;a&gt;Tab 3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
            &lt;/ul&gt;

            &lt;div&gt;Content for Tab 1&lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div&gt;Content for Tab 2&lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div&gt;Content for Tab 3&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
    </code></pre>
</div>

<div class="x-block-full">
    <h2 class="x-h2">Creating Addons</h2>
    <p>Addons are created using the <a class="x-link" href="/extend">extend method</a>.  Instead of extending widgets, addons extend from other addon modules:</p>

    <pre><code>
        define('my_addon', ['jquery', 'addons/base'], function($, Addon){
            var MyAddon = Addon.extend(function(){
                // constructor functionality
            });

            return MyAddon;
        });
    </code></pre>
</div>